    "reasoning": "First, determine the number of games Jackie played before her last game. Let \( n \) be the number of games before the last game. Her total points before the last game were \( 20n \). After scoring 36 points in the last game, her total points became \( 20n + 36 \) over \( n + 1 \) games, with an average of 21. Solving \( \\frac{20n + 36}{n + 1} = 21 \) gives \( n = 15 \). Thus, total points after the last game (total_after) is \( 20 \\times 15 + 36 = 336 \).\n\nNext, for Lauren's baskets: each basket is either 2 points or \( \\text{total\\_after} - 333 = 336 - 333 = 3 \) points. Let \( x \) be the number of 3-point baskets and \( y \) the number of 2-point baskets. We have \( x + y = 10 \) and \( 3x + 2y = 26 \). Substituting \( y = 10 - x \) into the second equation gives \( 3x + 2(10 - x) = 26 \), simplifying to \( x = 6 \).",
    "answer": "6"
